cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PF

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with modelling flow characteristics of Internet traffic. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as understanding traffic characteristics is important for security purposes. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with analysing network traffic. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Performance (cs.PF) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with assessing the efficiency of flow-oriented networking mechanisms and modelling traffic for performance evaluation.
